<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-1060] Attempting to returning a list over RMI/IIOP results in serialization exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-1060</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Returning a result list over RMI/IIOP invocation currently fails on trunk/2.0 with this exception:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.rmi.ServerException: RemoteException occurred in server thread; nested exception is: java.rmi.MarshalException: CORBA BAD_PARAM 0x4f4d0006 Maybe; nested exception is: java.io.NotSerializableException: org.apache.openjpa.jdbc.kernel.InstanceResultObjectProvider is not serializable at com.ibm.CORBA.iiop.UtilDelegateImpl.wrapException(UtilDelegateImpl.java:748) at javax.rmi.CORBA.Util.wrapException(Util.java:296) at ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem is the result of storing the ROP in the userObject field of a ResultList in the org.apache.openjpa.kernel.QueryImpl.toResult(..) method.  - res.setUserObject(rop).  The ROP is not serializable so the RMI/CORBA layer throws an exception.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
